Source attribution
==================

Vocabulary, example sentences, and lesson structure are adapted from
"Maryknoll Taiwanese Book 1", published by the Maryknoll Language Service
Center, Taichung, Taiwan. The Maryknoll dictionary materials from which
this work draws were released by Maryknoll under the Creative Commons
Attribution-NonCommercial-ShareAlike 3.0 license. This derivative work is
distributed under CC BY-NC-SA 4.0, which is a permitted ShareAlike-
compatible upgrade.

Modifications include: re-tabulation as Anki note CSVs; addition of
tone-sandhi numbering; selection of Taiwan Ministry of Education (MOE)
recommended Taiwanese Hàn-jī forms; and packaging as Anki .apkg decks.
